1.00	Boquerones	Boquerones en vinagre	Boquerones en vinagre are a type of appetizer or tapa frequently found in the south of Spain. The central ingredient of the dish is boquerones; fresh anchovies whose fillets have been marinated in vinegar, garlic, and parsley. It is commonly served with beer or soft drinks, and rarely with wine.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/50/Boquerones_en_vinagre-Madrid.jpg/220px-Boquerones_en_vinagre-Madrid.jpg
